Note-Taking Application

Note-Taking Application
This is a Java-based note-taking application that allows users to create, manage, and store notes. The application uses a MySQL database for storing the notes and leverages JDBC (Java Database Connectivity) for database operations.

Features
Create Notes: Users can create and save text notes.
Manage Notes: Users can edit or delete existing notes.
View Notes: Users can view a list of all saved notes.
MySQL Database Integration: All notes are stored in a MySQL database for persistent storage.
Technologies Used
Java: The core programming language used for the application.
JDBC: Used to establish a connection between the Java application and the MySQL database.
MySQL: The relational database management system used to store notes.
Swing : Used for creating the GUI.

Setup Instructions

Before running the application, these 4 must be installed

Java Development Kit (JDK) - Version 22 or higher(cause i used version 22 to make it.)
MySQL Server - Ensure that MySQL server is running and accessible
MySQL Connector/J - The JDBC driver for MySQL
IDE - An Integrated Development Environment  Eclipse(I RECOMMEND IT FOR EASE OF USE BUT DEFINETLY WORK ON OTHER IDE'S TOO.)
